An example would be, so one of the very first formal systems was the system

01:31:48.520 --> 01:31:54.360
was Euclidean Geometry, developed by Euclid in his famous book Elements about 2200 years ago.

01:31:55.480 --> 01:32:00.280
And it's about, well, it's a subject familiar from school because we studied,

