01:34:24.440 --> 01:34:25.800
meaning that doesn't intersect it.

01:34:27.160 --> 01:34:31.320
And Euclide himself was uncomfortable about this because he felt that it was kind of,

01:34:32.600 --> 01:34:35.960
you know, he takes for granted something that is not obvious.

01:34:35.960 --> 01:34:43.880
And for many centuries after that, mathematicians were trying to derive this axiom from other

01:34:43.880 --> 01:34:46.600
